<h1>Evidence Index</h1>
<p>Use this list to organize your supporting documents when lodging your Simple Procedure claim.</p>

<h2>Core documents to attach</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Tenancy agreement dated {{tenancy_start_date}} showing the agreed rent and payment terms</li>
  <li>Schedule of rent arrears with bank statements or rent ledger highlighting payments received</li>
  <li>Letters, emails or texts showing attempts to resolve the dispute before raising court proceedings</li>
  <li>Demand letters or payment reminders sent to the defender</li>
  {{#if damage_items.length}}
  <li>Photographs of property damage with repair quotes or invoices</li>
  {{/if}}
  {{#if other_charges.length}}
  <li>Receipts and invoices for other sums claimed (e.g., locksmith, cleaning)</li>
  {{/if}}
  <li>Tenancy deposit scheme registration certificate (if applicable)</li>
  <li>Copy of this statement of claim and particulars</li>
  <li>Interest calculation sheet</li>
</ol>

<h2>Additional helpful evidence</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Inventory and check-in report showing initial property condition</li>
  <li>Inspection notes or check-out report documenting damage</li>
  <li>Any correspondence with the defender about arrears or damage</li>
  <li>Witness statements from property managers or neighbours (if relevant)</li>
</ul>

<p>
  <strong>Important:</strong> Tick each item before lodging to ensure the Sheriff Court receives a complete bundle.
  Missing evidence can delay proceedings or weaken your claim. The sheriff may request additional documents at the hearing.
</p>
